The project uses custom MDX components for documentation with specific styling conventions:

## Component Styling

1. All components extend `fumadocs-ui/mdx` default components
2. Components use Tailwind CSS for styling
3. Common styling patterns:
   - Article wrapper: Full width flex column with gap-6
   - Code blocks: Muted background, rounded corners, monospace font
   - Headings: Bold with specific size hierarchy
   - Lists: Disc style with padding and gap
   - Links: Primary color, bold, underlined

## Component Reference

Key components and their styling:
- `wrapper`: Article container with flex column layout
- `code`: Inline code with muted background
- `h1`: Large headings (2xl) with bottom border
- `h2`: Medium headings (lg) with bottom border
- `h3`: Small headings (md) with bold weight
- `ul`: Disc-style lists with padding
- `a`: Primary-colored underlined links

Reference [mdx-components.tsx](mdc:src/mdx-components.tsx) for implementation details.
